		networkNumberOfIPv4Interfaces OBJECT-TYPE
			SYNTAX Integer32
			MAX-ACCESS read-only
			STATUS current
			DESCRIPTION
				"Number of IPv4 network like interfaces.
				
				If there's no active IPv4 interfaces, then 1 interface should be reported with type N/A (networkInterfaceTypeNA(255))."
			::= { networkIPv4 1 }

		
		-- 1.3.6.1.4.1.3715.100.104.1.2
		networkIPv4InterfaceGlobalServicesEnable OBJECT-TYPE
			SYNTAX NetworkInterfaceServices
			MAX-ACCESS read-only
			STATUS current
			DESCRIPTION
				"IPv4 services control method per service.
				
				Global services (per device)
				If service bit is set (at networkIPv4InterfaceGlobalServicesEnable), service supports only global (per device) control and does not support per interface/per port control.
				Global service state should be get and set (enabled/disabled) by using port that supports this service (indicated in networkIPv4InterfaceServices). So when changing global
				service state using one port, result is seen in all other ports. Device may support global service control by using any port.
				
				Per port services
				If service bit is cleared (networkIPv4InterfaceGlobalServicesEnable), service supports per interface/per port control.
				Per port service state is get and set (enabled/disabled) by using spesific port networkIPv4InterfaceServices.
				
				NOTE! Changing IPv4 services may affect IPv6 services too. This is device dependant."
			::= { networkIPv4 2 }

		
